div.p:
The answer was given to the fourteen-year-old boy in the woods of western New York when
the Lord declared, "They draw near to me with their lips, but their hearts are far from me;
they teach for doctrines the commandments of men, having a form of godliness, but they deny
the power thereof" (see
Isa. 29:13;
Matt. 15:8;
2 Tim. 3:5;
JS—H 1:19).
